data.text:
Full Name: Richard Bruce Cheney

Profession: 46th Vice President of the United States

Biography: Cheney served Vice President of the United States under George W. Bush (2001-2009). In this position he was crucial to the conduct of both the War in Afghanistan and the Iraq War, as well as coordinating operations associated with the Global War on Terror.

Cheney was often criticized for his policies regarding wiretapping by the National Security Agency and so-called enhanced interrogation techniques. He is widely considered one of the most powerful Vice Presidents in American history.

Outside of his policies he became infamous for shooting a fellow hunter on a quail hunt at Armstrong ranch in Texas.

Born: January 30, 1941

Birthplace: Lincoln, Nebraska, USA

Age: 83 years old
